# RULES

## source_type
Detect from URL/domain. Use exactly one of:
github_repo | youtube_video | huggingface_model | article | documentation | other

## URL
Priority:
1. og:url
2. metadata url
3. input URL

## Title
Priority:
1. og:title
2. title
3. first H1
4. domain

Cleaning rules — apply strictly in order:
1. Strip "GitHub - owner/repo: " prefix
2. Strip " · GitHub", " - GitHub", " | GitHub", " | YouTube" suffixes
3. For GitHub repos: if result is still longer than 60 chars, extract repo name from nwo field
4. For YouTube: keep video title as-is after suffix stripping
5. Max 60 characters. Hard limit. Cut at last full word if needed.

## Person
Primary identity of publisher:
- GitHub -> repository owner from octolytics-dimension-user_login or nwo prefix
- YouTube -> channel name from metadata
- HuggingFace -> model owner from URL path
- Other -> og:site_name or domain

## Cover
Absolute URL only.
Priority:
1. og:image
2. twitter:image
3. any absolute image URL in metadata
If none -> ""

## Raw metadata
One factual line only.
Only confirmed facts.
Never say "not stated".

Examples:
- GitHub repository msitarzewski/agency-agents; public; not forked.
- YouTube video; channel: Tranquility Music.
- HuggingFace model nvidia/parakeet-ctc-1.1b.

## description_for_classifier
Clean text for downstream classifier.
Combine in order, separated by " | ":
1. og:description or description, trimmed to 300 chars
2. source_type
3. Person

Strip HTML and boilerplate.

## Other fields
- Like -> false
- Saved -> USER_MESSAGE with URL removed and spaces normalized
- Tags -> []
- facet_format -> []
